In[7]:
df = pl.read_csv("dataset/cleaned_data.csv") \
    .filter(pl.col("StationId").is_in(stations)) \
    .with_columns(pl.col('Date').str.to_datetime().cast(pl.Date)) \
    .filter(pl.col("Date") >= pl.lit("2017-11-01").cast(pl.Date)) \
    .filter(pl.col("Date") <= pl.lit("2020-06-30").cast(pl.Date)) \
    .with_columns(pl.col("Date").dt.month().alias("Month")) \
    .with_columns(pl.col("Date").dt.year().alias("Year")) \
    .with_columns(pl.col("Date").dt.day().alias("Day")) \
    .with_columns(pl.concat_str([pl.col("Year"), pl.col("Month")], separator="-").alias("Year-Month")) \
    .sort("Year", "Month", "Day", "StationId")

date_range = list(dict.fromkeys(df["Year-Month"].to_list()))

df_monthly = df.group_by("StationId", "Year-Month", "Month", "Year") \
    .agg([pl.col(metric).mean().alias(metric) for metric in air_metrics]) \
    .sort("Year", "Month")

def get_stats(air_metric):
    return df.group_by("StationId").agg([
        pl.col(air_metric).mean().alias(air_metric+"_mean"),
        pl.col(air_metric).median().alias(air_metric+"_median"),
        pl.col(air_metric).std().alias(air_metric+"_std"),
        pl.col(air_metric).var().alias(air_metric+"_var"),
        pl.col(air_metric).min().alias(air_metric+"_min"),
        pl.col(air_metric).max().alias(air_metric+"_max")
    ])

for air_metric in air_metrics:
    print(get_stats(air_metric))

4. Time Series Plots

In[9]:
def plot_time_series(df, x, frequency, rotate=False):
    for air_metric in air_metrics:
        plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
        sns.lineplot(
            data=df, 
            x=x, 
            y=air_metric, 
            hue='StationId',
            palette = colors
        )
        
        plt.title(f'Time Series of {air_metric} at 4 Different Stations in Delhi ({frequency})')
        plt.ylabel(air_metric)
        plt.xlabel("")
        if rotate:
            plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
In[10]:
plot_time_series(df=df, x='Date', frequency='Daily', rotate=False)
In[11]:

In[12]:
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
for metric in air_metrics:
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(stations), 1, figsize=(10, 8), sharex=True)
    color_patches = [mpatches.Patch(color=colors[i % len(colors)], label=f'{station_id}')
                     for i, station_id in enumerate(stations)]
    for count, (station_id, ax) in enumerate(zip(stations, axes)):
        sns.barplot(
            x="Year-Month", y=metric, data=df_monthly, ax=ax, color=colors[count % len(colors)], errorbar=None
        )
        ax.set_xlabel("")
        ax.set_ylabel("")
    for ax in axes:
        ax.set_xticks(range(0, len(date_range), 6))
    fig.legend(handles=color_patches, loc='upper right', title="Stations", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), bbox_transform=plt.gcf().transFigure)
    fig.suptitle(f"{metric} in Delhi from 2017/10 - 2020/07", fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

6. Correlation Analysis

In[28]:
def plot_heatmap(corr_df, labels, title):

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.heatmap(corr_df, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', vmin=-1, vmax=1, linewidths=0.5,
                xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels)
    plt.title(title, fontsize=14)
    plt.show()
In[29]:
correlation_matrix = df[air_metrics].corr()

plot_heatmap(correlation_matrix, air_metrics, 'Correlation Heatmap of Air Quality Metrics')

df_s1 = df.filter(pl.col("StationId") == stations[0]) \
    .select("Date", "PM2.5", "PM10", "NOx", "CO", "SO2", "O3") \
    .rename({"PM2.5": "PM2.5_DL002", "PM10": "PM10_DL002", "NOx": "NOx_DL002", "CO": "CO_DL002", "SO2": "SO2_DL002", "O3": "O3_DL002"})
df_s2 = df.filter(pl.col("StationId") == stations[1]) \
    .select("Date", "PM2.5", "PM10", "NOx", "CO", "SO2", "O3") \
    .rename({"PM2.5": "PM2.5_DL019", "PM10": "PM10_DL019", "NOx": "NOx_DL019", "CO": "CO_DL019", "SO2": "SO2_DL019", "O3": "O3_DL019"})
df_s3 = df.filter(pl.col("StationId") == stations[2]) \
    .select("Date", "PM2.5", "PM10", "NOx", "CO", "SO2", "O3") \
    .rename({"PM2.5": "PM2.5_DL028", "PM10": "PM10_DL028", "NOx": "NOx_DL028", "CO": "CO_DL028", "SO2": "SO2_DL028", "O3": "O3_DL028"})
df_s4 = df.filter(pl.col("StationId") == stations[3]) \
    .select("Date", "PM2.5", "PM10", "NOx", "CO", "SO2", "O3") \
    .rename({"PM2.5": "PM2.5_DL031", "PM10": "PM10_DL031", "NOx": "NOx_DL031", "CO": "CO_DL031", "SO2": "SO2_DL031", "O3": "O3_DL031"})

df_station_free = df_s1.join(df_s2, on="Date", how="inner").join(df_s3, on="Date", how="inner").join(df_s4, on="Date", how="inner")

for air_metric in air_metrics:
    metric_columns = [f"{air_metric}_{station}" for station in stations]
    correlation_matrix = df_station_free[metric_columns].corr()

    plot_heatmap(correlation_matrix, stations, f'Correlation Heatmap of {air_metric} at the different stations')
